To integrate Wistia Uploader into an Angular 14 application, you'll need to follow several steps. Wistia provides a JavaScript library that can be used to upload videos directly from your web application to their servers. Here's how you can do it:

### Step 1: Install Dependencies

First, ensure you have Node.js and npm installed on your system. Then, create a new Angular project or navigate to your existing one.

If you're creating a new project:
```bash
ng new my-angular-app
cd my-angular-app
```

### Step 2: Add Wistia Uploader Script

Wistia doesn't provide an npm package for the uploader, so you'll need to include the script directly in your `index.html` file or via a script tag in your component.

Add the following line in your `src/index.html` file inside the `<head>` section:
```html
<script src="https://fast.wistia.com/static/EmbedUploader.min.js"></script>
```

Alternatively, you can dynamically load the script using Angular's `DomSanitizer` service.

### Step 3: Create a Component for Uploading

Create a new component where you will implement the video upload functionality.
```bash
ng generate component VideoUpload
```

In your `video-upload.component.ts`, you can set up the basic structure of your component:
```typescript
import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-video-upload',
  templateUrl: './video-upload.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./video-upload.component.css']
})
export class VideoUploadComponent implements OnInit {
  constructor() {}

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.initializeUploader();
  }

  initializeUploader() {
    const options = {
      // Your Wistia Project ID
      projectId: 'your-project-id',
      // Optional callback functions
      onProgress: function (progress) {
        console.log('Upload progress:', progress);
      },
      onComplete: function (response) {
        console.log('Upload complete:', response);
      }
    };

    const uploader = new WistiaUploader(options);
    uploader.init();
  }
}
```

### Step 4: Update Template

Update your template (`video-upload.component.html`) to include the upload button:
```html
<button id="upload-button">Upload Video</button>

<script>
  document.getElementById('upload-button').addEventListener('click', function () {
    window.uploader.open();
  });
</script>
```

### Step 5: Configure Styles (Optional)

You might want to add some styles to your `video-upload.component.css` to make the button look better.

### Step 6: Use the Component

Finally, include your `VideoUploadComponent` in the desired module and add its selector to the appropriate HTML file where you want the upload feature to appear.

### Note
- Replace `'your-project-id'` with your actual Wistia project ID.
- The `WistiaUploader` object is globally available after including the Wistia script.
- Ensure that your Wistia account has the necessary permissions to upload videos programmatically.

This setup should allow you to start integrating Wistia Uploader into your Angular 14 application. Make sure to check Wistia’s official documentation for more detailed configuration options and best practices.

