To integrate the Castlabs SDK into your Android application using Kotlin, and to fetch cookies via Retrofit before starting the video player, you can follow these steps:

### Step 1: Add Dependencies
First, ensure that you have added the necessary dependencies in your `build.gradle` file:

```gradle
dependencies {
    implementation 'com.squareup.retrofit2:retrofit:2.9.0'
    implementation 'com.squareup.retrofit2:converter-gson:2.9.0'
    implementation 'com.castlabs.android:player-sdk:latest_version' // Replace with the actual version number
}
```

### Step 2: Create ApiService Interface
Create an interface for Retrofit to handle API calls:

```kotlin
import retrofit2.Call
import retrofit2.http.GET
import retrofit2.http.Headers

interface ApiService {
    @Headers("Content-Type: application/json")
    @GET("/api/MediaStorage/GetCookies")
    fun getCookies(): Call<CookiesResponse>
}

data class CookiesResponse(val cookie: String)
```

### Step 3: Setup Retrofit
Initialize Retrofit and create an instance of `ApiService`:

```kotlin
import okhttp3.OkHttpClient
import retrofit2.Retrofit
import retrofit2.converter.gson.GsonConverterFactory

object ApiClient {
    private const val BASE_URL = "https://your-api-url.com/" // Replace with your actual API base URL

    private val client = OkHttpClient.Builder().build()

    private val retrofit = Retrofit.Builder()
        .baseUrl(BASE_URL)
        .addConverterFactory(GsonConverterFactory.create())
        .client(client)
        .build()

    val apiService: ApiService = retrofit.create(ApiService::class.java)
}
```

### Step 4: Modify MainActivity
Update `MainActivity` to fetch cookies and start the player with the fetched cookie:

```kotlin
import android.os.Bundle
import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity
import com.castlabs.android.player.PlayerController
import com.castlabs.android.player.PlayerConfig
import com.castlabs.android.player.view.PlayerView
import kotlinx.coroutines.*
import retrofit2.HttpException

class MainActivity : AppCompatActivity() {

    private lateinit var playerView: PlayerView

    override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)

        playerView = findViewById(R.id.player_view)

        fetchAndPlayVideo()
    }

    private fun fetchAndPlayVideo() {
        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.IO).launch {
            try {
                val response = ApiClient.apiService.getCookies().execute()
                if (response.isSuccessful && response.body() != null) {
                    val cookie = response.body()?.cookie ?: ""
                    withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {
                        startPlayback(cookie)
                    }
                } else {
                    withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {
                        showError(response.message())
                    }
                }
            } catch (e: HttpException) {
                withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {
                    showError(e.message ?: "Unknown error")
                }
            } catch (e: Exception) {
                withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {
                    showError(e.message ?: "Unknown error")
                }
            }
        }
    }

    private fun startPlayback(cookie: String) {
        val controller: PlayerController = playerView.playerController
        try {
            controller.open(
                PlayerConfig.Builder("https://media.elottdev.pp.ua/Rootd4ae5870-2996-4476-8ada-adf487a0ab71/elott-web/Arnold%20War%20in%20UA/manifests/master_manifest.m3u8")
                    .userID("1")
                    .headers(mapOf("Cookie" to cookie))
                    .get()
            )
        } catch (e: Exception) {
            Log.e("MainActivity", e.toString())
        }
    }

    private fun showError(message: String) {
        // Implement your error handling logic here
        Log.e("MainActivity", message)
    }

    override fun onStart() {
        super.onStart()
        playerView.lifecycleDelegate.start(this)
    }

    override fun onResume() {
        super.onResume()
        playerView.lifecycleDelegate.resume()
    }

    override fun onStop() {
        super.onStop()
        playerView.lifecycleDelegate.releasePlayer(false)
    }
}
```

### Step 5: Update ElottApplication
Ensure your `ElottApplication` is properly set up to initialize the Castlabs SDK:

```kotlin
class ElottApplication : Application() {

    override fun onCreate() {
        super.onCreate()
        try {
            PlayerSDK.init(applicationContext, CAST_LABS_LICENSE_KEY)
        } catch (e: Exception) {
            Log.e("ElottApplication", "Couldn't init Castlabs SDK: $e")
        }
    }

    companion object {
        const val CAST_LABS_LICENSE_KEY = "your_license_key_here" // Replace with your actual license key
    }
}
```

### Conclusion
This setup will allow you to fetch cookies from the API and use them to configure the Castlabs player in your Android app. Make sure to replace placeholder URLs and keys with actual values specific to your project.

