Creating a browser extension that links any string matching a Tezos wallet or contract address to `tzkt.io` involves several steps. Below is a simplified version of how you can achieve this using JavaScript and the Chrome Extension API. This example will focus on the basics: detecting Tezos addresses and linking them to `tzkt.io`.

### Step 1: Set Up Your Project

First, create a directory for your project and inside it, create these files:
- `manifest.json`
- `content.js`
- `popup.html` (optional, if you want a popup interface)
- `icon.png` (optional, an icon for your extension)

### Step 2: Write the Manifest File (`manifest.json`)

This file tells the browser about your extension and what permissions it needs.

```json
{
  "manifest_version": 3,
  "name": "Tezos Address Linker",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "Links Tezos wallet or contract addresses to tzkt.io",
  "permissions": [
    "activeTab"
  ],
  "content_scripts": [
    {
      "matches": ["<all_urls>"],
      "js": ["content.js"]
    }
  ],
  "icons": {
    "48": "icon.png"
  },
  "action": {
    "default_popup": "popup.html",
    "default_icon": {
      "48": "icon.png"
    }
  }
}
```

### Step 3: Create the Content Script (`content.js`)

This script will run in the context of web pages and look for Tezos addresses.

```javascript
function linkAddresses() {
  const textNodes = document.createTreeWalker(document.body, NodeFilter.SHOW_TEXT, null, false);

  while (textNodes.nextNode()) {
    let node = textNodes.currentNode;
    if (node.parentNode && node.parentNode.tagName.toLowerCase() !== 'script') {
      const text = node.textContent;
      const matches = text.match(/[tzKT1][a-km-zA-HJ-NP-Z1-9]{33}/g);

      if (matches) {
        // Wrap each match with an anchor tag pointing to tzkt.io
        matches.forEach(match => {
          const anchor = document.createElement('a');
          anchor.href = `https://tzkt.io/${match}`;
          anchor.textContent = match;
          anchor.target = '_blank';

          const span = document.createElement('span');
          span.innerHTML = text.replace(new RegExp(match, 'g'), anchor.outerHTML);
          node.parentNode.insertBefore(span, node);
          node.parentNode.removeChild(node);
        });
      }
    }
  }
}

linkAddresses();
```

### Step 4: Optional - Create a Popup Interface (`popup.html`)

If you want users to interact with your extension through a popup, you can add a simple HTML file for this purpose.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Tezos Address Linker</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Tezos Address Linker</h1>
  <p>This extension links Tezos addresses to tzkt.io.</p>
</body>
</html>
```

### Step 5: Add an Icon (`icon.png`)

Add an icon for your extension. This is optional but recommended for a better user experience.

### Step 6: Load Your Extension into Chrome

1. Open Chrome and go to `chrome://extensions/`.
2. Enable Developer mode.
3. Click on "Load unpacked" and select your extension's directory.

Now, your extension should be active and automatically detect and link Tezos addresses on any webpage to `tzkt.io`. Adjust the regular expression in the content script as needed to improve detection accuracy based on the specific format of Tezos addresses you're targeting.

